---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | pedestrianaccidentcalc.com';
const description = 'Privacy policy for pedestrianaccidentcalc.com — what data we collect, how we use it, and your options for limiting data collection.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 2026</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>Browsing pedestrianaccidentcalc.com and using the settlement calculator collects nothing personally identifying — the calculator processes all inputs locally in your browser, and no settlement inputs, injury severity, or fault percentages are transmitted to our servers or to any third party. Separately, if you choose to submit the case-review form on our homepage, that form does collect personal information, described below.</p>

  <h2>Information Collected If You Submit the Case-Review Form</h2>
  <p>The homepage includes an optional "Pedestrian Accident" case-review form. If you fill it out and submit it, we collect your name, phone number, email address, the case details you provide, and a timestamp of your consent. Nothing is collected through this form unless you actively submit it.</p>

  <h2>How That Information Is Used and Shared</h2>
  <p>If you submit the case-review form, your name, phone number, email address, and case details are shared with one or more attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you about it. The Click Lab Agency LLC, which operates pedestrianaccidentcalc.com, is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice, and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals.</p>
  <p>By submitting the form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email — including by automated dialing technology — by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That consent is not required to use any other part of this site, and you can decline it by not submitting the form.</p>

  <h2>Your Opt-Out Options</h2>
  <p>The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form — nothing in the rest of the site depends on it. If you already submitted the form and want to withdraw consent or have your information deleted, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <strong>[OPT-OUT]</strong>, or visit <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>.</p>

  <h2>California Residents (CCPA/CPRA)</h2>
  <p>Sharing your information with attorneys in exchange for compensation, as described above, may constitute a "sale" or "share" of personal information under the California Consumer Privacy Act and CPRA. California residents can opt out of this sharing at any time using either channel in the section above. Browsing the site and using the calculator without submitting the case-review form is never sold or shared, because we don't collect any personal information from that activity in the first place.</p>

  <h2>European Residents (GDPR)</h2>
  <p>If you are in the European Economic Area or UK, the legal basis for processing your information when you submit the case-review form is your consent — given when you check the consent box and submit the form. You can withdraw that consent at any time using the opt-out channels above; withdrawing consent does not affect the lawfulness of any sharing that already occurred before withdrawal.</p>

  <h2>Google AdSense</h2>
  <p>This site displays advertising through Google AdSense (publisher ID: ca-pub-6434377544325972). Google AdSense uses cookies to serve interest-based advertising. You can opt out via <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ad Settings</a>. Google's data practices are governed by <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>Google Analytics</h2>
  <p>We use Google Analytics (measurement ID G-QCPFPB1CHD) for aggregate traffic analysis. Google Analytics does not identify individual users. You can opt out using the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.</p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>Cookies are placed by Google AdSense and Google Analytics. We do not place first-party cookies beyond basic site functionality. You can manage cookie settings in your browser.</p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>This site is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly collect information from children.</p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>Material changes will be noted with an updated date above. Questions? Email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
